    {
      "id": "facsimile-images",
      "html": "<h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001306_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001306_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001306.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001306-thumb.jpg\"></a>"
    },
    {
      "id": "apparatus",
      "html": "<h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text based on photographs</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"line 5\">line.5: <span>Kaibel saw an ivy leaf at the end of the line, but it rather seems to be a triangle-shaped interpunct.</span>  </span></li></ul>"
    },
    {
      "id": "translation",
      "html": "<h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo</a></p>  <p>To the underworld spirits. Kassia Benousta, lived for 11 years, 9 months, and 8 days. Her father and mother made this for their sweetest child.</p>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "translation",
      "html": "<h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo</a></p>  <p>Agli Dei inferi. Kassia Benousta visse 11 anni, 9 mesi e 8 giorni. Suo padre e sua madre realizzarono questo per la loro dolce figlia.</p>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "commentary",
      "html": "<h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The structure of the epitaph is the most frequent in pagan epitaphs, with the invocation to the underworld spirits, the name of the deceased in the nominative form, his/her age, the name of the dedicants (in this case, the parents) and the dedication verb in aorist (Korhonen 2004: 85-86). An interesting linguistic detail is the indication of months and days in the nominative and not in the accusative form (<span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μῆνες, ἡμέρες</span>), which seems to be due to confusion with Latin where the nominative and accusative plural of <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">mensis</span> and <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">dies</span> correspond: for a similar confusion, see also SEG 44.0762 = <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000641\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000641</a>. On the name <span class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Βενοῦστα</span>, see SEG 29.931-3 (from Morgantina, 1st century CE). Note too the spelling out of the first numeral in full, rather than using the standard alphabetic notation.</p>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "bibliography",
      "html": "<h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li></li><li> Spuches 1864 13 no.3 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042</a>  </li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">483</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a>  </li><li> Korhonen 2004 67 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li> Korhonen 2004 85-86 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</a>  </li></ul>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "handnote",
      "html": " <p>Regular letters: rhomboid Θ, Ο, Ω (open); Α with accentuated upper serif, Μ with slanting full-length bars (but irregular), Υ with an extended right arm (line 6), ΗΝΕ at l. 4 and ΤΗ at l. 5 (x2) in ligature. In the last line, some letters are smaller than others for lack of space.</p> Lines 1-6  20-25  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not registered  "
    },
